---
# Cline Rules Configuration
# This file configures bmad (Business Model Analysis and Design) integration with Cline

# BMAD Integration Configuration
bmad:
  enabled: true
  version: "v1"
  root: "_bmad"  # Path to bmad installation
  workflows: "_bmad/_config/bmad-help.csv"  # Workflow definitions
  agents: "_bmad/_config/agents"  # Agent configurations
  modules:
    - "_bmad/bmb"  # Builder module
    - "_bmad/bmm"  # Business module
    - "_bmad/cis"  # Creative innovation system
    - "_bmad/core"  # Core utilities
    - "_bmad/tea"  # Testing and automation

# Workflow Discovery
workflowDiscovery:
  enabled: true
  directories:
    - "_bmad"
    - ".agent"

# MCP (Model Context Protocol) Configuration
mcp:
  servers:
    - name: "github.com/upstash/context7-mcp"
      command: "npx"
      args: ["-y", "@upstash/context7-mcp"]
      autoApprove: ["resolve-library-id"]
    - name: "github.com/parallel-web/search-mcp"
      url: "https://search-mcp.parallel.ai/mcp"

# Default Agent Configuration
defaultAgents:
  analyst: "_bmad/bmm/agents/analyst.md"
  architect: "_bmad/bmm/agents/architect.md"
  dev: "_bmad/bmm/agents/dev.md"
  pm: "_bmad/bmm/agents/pm.md"
  ux-designer: "_bmad/bmm/agents/ux-designer.md"
  tech-writer: "_bmad/bmm/agents/tech-writer/tech-writer.md"
  qa: "_bmad/bmm/agents/quinn.md"

# Output Configuration
output:
  planning: "_bmad-output/planning-artifacts"
  implementation: "_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts"
  testing: "_bmad-output/testing-artifacts"

# Enable BMAD Help System
help:
  enabled: true
  file: "_bmad/core/tasks/help.md"
---

BMAD (Business Model Analysis and Design) is now integrated with Cline in this repository. To use bmad, you can:

## Quick Start

1. **Get Help**: `/bmad-help` - Show available workflows and next steps
2. **Quick Spec**: `/bmad-quick-spec` - Rapid specification for simple tasks
3. **Quick Dev**: `/bmad-quick-dev` - Rapid development for small changes

## Available Modules

### bmm (Business Management Module)
- `/bmad-bmm-research` - Market/domain/technical research
- `/bmad-bmm-create-prd` - Create Product Requirements Document
- `/bmad-bmm-create-architecture` - Create technical architecture
- `/bmad-bmm-sprint-planning` - Plan development sprints
- `/bmad-bmm-dev-story` - Execute story implementation

### bmb (Builder Module)
- `/bmad-bmb-agent` - Create/edit/validate agents
- `/bmad-bmb-module` - Create/edit/validate modules
- `/bmad-bmb-workflow` - Create/edit/validate workflows

### cis (Creative Innovation System)
- `/bmad-cis-design-thinking` - Human-centered design
- `/bmad-cis-problem-solving` - Systematic problem-solving
- `/bmad-cis-brainstorming` - Idea generation sessions
- `/bmad-cis-storytelling` - Compelling narrative creation

### tea (Testing and Automation)
- `/bmad_tea_framework` - Initialize test framework
- `/bmad_tea_atdd` - Generate failing tests (TDD red phase)
- `/bmad_tea_automate` - Expand test coverage
- `/bmad_tea_test-review` - Quality audit

### core (Essential Utilities)
- `/bmad-brainstorming` - Interactive brainstorming
- `/bmad-party-mode` - Multi-agent discussions
- `/bmad-index-docs` - Quick document indexing
- `/bmad-editorial-review-prose` - Content review

## Usage Examples

- To start planning your project: `/bmad-bmm-research`
- To create product specifications: `/bmad-bmm-create-prd`
- To start sprint planning: `/bmad-bmm-sprint-planning`
- To develop a feature: `/bmad-bmm-dev-story`
- To add test coverage: `/bmad_tea_automate`

## Configuration Details

BMAD will:
1. Load workflows from `_bmad/_config/bmad-help.csv`
2. Use agents defined in `_bmad/bmm/agents/`
3. Store outputs in `_bmad-output/` directory
4. Automatically manage phase transitions

For detailed help: `/bmad-help`